-- Brazil to Offer 16% Pay Increase to Civil Servants, Estado Says
-- B y   R o d r i g o   O r i h u e l a
-- 2012-08-18T13:01:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-18/brazil-to-offer-16-pay-increase-to-civil-servants-estado-says.html
Brazil will offer 15.8 percent
salary increases to striking civil workers, newspaper O Estado
de Sao Paulo reported, citing union official Josemilton Costa.  The pay increase was offered to 18 of the 36 civil servant
categories that are striking, the Sao Paulo-based newspaper
reported. The government also offered a 15.8 percent pay raise
to federal police workers, after they struck for 24 hours this
week, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rodrigo Orihuela in  Rio de Janeiro  at 
